headline: What Do Kroger’s Layoffs Mean for Its Stock Value in 2025?
summary: Trying to decide what to do with Kroger stock right now? You are far from alone. The company has had a year full of headline-making moments, with moves in its share price that have grabbed the attention of long-term investors and newcomers alike. In the past year, KR has delivered a strong 24.9% return, handily beating the S&P 500. Even over longer periods, the track record is impressive, up 67.9% over three years and 121.4% over five.
